@0 block stack v2
@1 $2^16$ words, 1024 block of 64 words
@2 10 bits for block address
@3 block offset addressing
@4 fixed size linked list array
@5 A[node] $=$ next
@6 0 is null
@7 can be implemented in 10-bit array
@9 packed bits: 10-bits, 1024 entries = 5 blocks
@8 block stack implementation
@a general purpose bit array
@b build on top of bit array
@c global array: $2^16$ times 32 bits
@d $2^16 \cdot 2^5 = 2^21$, addressing fits in 32-bit word
@e sub-arrays: global offset + local index
@f operations
@g set: A, start, size, data
@h get: A, start, size
@i compute end addr
@j determine word bounds
@k num $W_a$ bits: $(W_a + 1)\cdot 32 - size$
@l num $W_b$ bits: $(W_b + 1)\cdot 32$
@m only needed if $W_a \neq W_b$
@n 32 size max
@o $W_a = \lfloor start / 32 \rfloor$, $W_b = \lfloor end / 32 \rfloor$
@p write $n_A$ bits to $W_a$, starting at offset $i_a$
@q $i_a = start - W_a$
@r $n_b$ bits to $W_b$ = start at $i_b$.
@s $i_b$ = end - $W_b$
@t end = start + size
@u exclusive bound?
@v append $n_A$ bits from $W_a[i_a:i_a + n_a]$ to 0
@w append: $O <<= n, O |= x ^ (1 << (n - 1))$
@x append $n_b$ bits from $w_b$ region to $O$
@y return $O$
